   {:e #blake3 "202fa8e9b3867136daab42895c166bb2c5dde5c08edc20bedf260430aef4e3f8" :a :task/description :v "CONTEXT: The definitive test of braid's core hypothesis: does the system learn across sessions? And does it ASCEND the epistemological stack?\n\nTHE STACK:\n  Observations -> raw facts (datoms)\n  Concepts -> clusters of observations (emergent categories)\n  Theories -> relationships between concepts (the co-occurrence topology)\n  Predictions -> falsifiable claims derived from theories (hypothesis ledger)\n  Paradigms -> meta-structure: the pattern of patterns that generalizes across projects\n\nPROTOCOL (3 sequential subagent sessions on Go CLI):\n\nSession 1 (Agent 1 — cold start):\n- Fresh braid init (no innate concepts)\n- 10 observations exploring freely\n- Harvest -> concepts crystallize from observations\n- Record: packages covered, surprise per observation, concepts formed, topological events\n\nSession 2 (Agent 2 — seeded from Session 1):\n- Same .braid/ directory (concepts, calibration, observations persist)\n- 10 observations, guided by emergent concepts + discrepancy steering\n- Harvest -> concepts refine, theories emerge (concept relationships visible)\n- Record: same metrics + concept topology changes\n\nSession 3 (Agent 3 — seeded from Sessions 1+2):\n- Same .braid/ directory (accumulated knowledge)\n- 10 observations, guided by theory-level steering\n- Record: same metrics + topology shifts + paradigm-level insights\n\nCONVERGENCE METRICS:\n\n(A) Surprise trajectory: mean surprise per session should DECREASE.\n(B) Coverage rate: unique packages per observation should INCREASE.\n(C) Silence ratio: fraction of one-line confirms should INCREASE.\n(D) EPISTEMOLOGICAL ASCENT (new):\n  Tag each observation by level using the data we collect:\n  - CONCEPT-LEVEL: joins ONE concept, low surprise (<0.3), no topo event\n  - THEORY-LEVEL: joins 2+ concepts OR bridges disconnected concepts (topo event without topology shift)\n  - PARADIGM-LEVEL: high surprise (>0.5) + topological event (the observation contradicts the current theory structure)\n  Measure: fraction of theory+paradigm level observations should INCREASE across sessions. Session 1 = mostly concept-level. Session 3 = mostly theory-level with paradigm insights.\n\n(E) Qualitative: Does Agent 3 articulate architectural PATTERNS ('this follows event-sourcing with a materialization boundary') rather than just package descriptions ('storage uses SQLite')?\n\nSCORING:\n  Converging on A-D + E affirmative = PASS (braid learns AND ascends)\n  Converging on A-C but flat on D = PARTIAL (learns but doesn't ascend — theories don't emerge)\n  Flat on all = FAIL (harvest/seed broken)\n  Diverging = HARMFUL\n\nSUBAGENT PROMPT: Identical across all 3 sessions. Agent should NOT be told about the epistemological stack — the ascent must be emergent, not prompted. The prompt says: 'explore the Go CLI codebase using braid, make 10 observations, follow braid's guidance.' That's it.\n\nDEPENDS-ON: INQ-TEST." :op :assert}
